{"title":"Vignesh Gopakumar","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Vignesh Gopakumar","image":"Images/IAEA_London.png","about":{"template":"trestles","links":[{"text":"LinkedIn","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/vignesh-gopakumar/","icon":"linkedin"},{"text":"Twitter (X)","url":"https://x.com/mistervickster","icon":"twitter"},{"text":"Scholar","url":"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=NQtqemwAAAAJ&hl=en","icon":"google-scholar"},{"text":"GitHub","icon":"github","url":"https://github.com/gitvicky"},{"text":"Email","url":"mailto:vignesh7g@gmail.com","icon":"mail"}]},"comments":false},"headingText":"Current Research:","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n::: {.center}\n***Can AI learn to obey physics?***\n:::\n\nI am a Research Scientist at the [UK Atomic Energy Authority](https://ccfe.ukaea.uk/) (UKAEA), where I lead a team developing \"actionable\" surrogate models for exascale simulations and data-driven models for the Fusion industry. My research focusses on enhancing machine learning models' performance, robustness and interpretability through physics-based approaches. \n\nI am also a visiting researcher with the [SciML group at STFC's Rutherford Appleton Laboratory](https://www.scd.stfc.ac.uk/Pages/Scientific-Machine-Learning.aspx). \n\nConcurrently, I'm pursuing a PhD in Machine Learning under [Marc Deisenroth](https://www.deisenroth.cc/) at [University College London](https://www.ucl.ac.uk/ai-centre/).\n\nCurrent Hot Take: \"The world would be so much better if we could just invert these matrices.\" \n\n\n* Physics-Informed Machine Learning\n* Continuous Dynamics Modelling\n* Uncertainty Quantification\n* Design of Experiments\n\n**Building [simvue.io](https://simvue.io)** : AI-driven, open-source simulation management and tracking dashboard for streamlining engineering workflows. Developed with public funding from the UK Government. Currently in private $\\beta$. \n\n> *\"If there is a God, it must be a differential equation\"* - Bertrand Russell\n","srcMarkdownN